=== CONFIDENCE SCORING ===

For each row, assign a confidence level:
- "High": Marks are clearly legible with no ambiguity (>80% certain)
- "Medium": Marks are readable but some ambiguity exists (50-80% certain)
- "Low": Marks are very difficult to read or ambiguous (<50% certain)

Factors that reduce confidence:
- Smudged or faded ink
- Overlapping tally marks
- Marks near column boundaries
- Very dense tallies that are hard to separate
- Possible water damage or creasing

=== IMPORTANT RULES ===

1. Include ALL species rows, even those with zero counts (output 0 for empty cells)
2. EXPAND all abbreviated genus names to their full form
3. For ditto marks (") or ('), use the last full value from the row above
4. Read left-to-right across size columns carefully — do not skip columns
5. Double-check tallies of 5+ by counting individual strokes
6. If a cell is genuinely empty/blank, record 0
7. If you cannot read a cell at all, record -1 and set confidence to "Low"
8. Note any handwritten additions, corrections, or crossed-out entries
9. Return ONLY the JSON object — no markdown, no explanation, no backticks

=== KNOWN QUIRKS & SURVEYOR VARIATIONS ===

(Add entries here as you encounter patterns across different datasheets)

- Some surveyors write tallies as dots instead of strokes for <10cm fish
- "A. Sohal" is sometimes capitalised as a common name; treat as Acanthurus sohal
- Site codes may use dots (FN0003.01) or underscores (FN0003_01); preserve as written
- Current may be recorded as a slash "/" meaning nil/none, or descriptive text
- Date format varies: DD/MM/YY is standard but some use MM/DD/YY — use context
  (Red Sea surveys = DD/MM/YY convention)
- The "Transect: (..../.....)" header sometimes has the number filled in,
  sometimes left blank — cross-reference with filename if available
- Incidental sightings section may contain species not in the standard list;
  transcribe species names exactly as written

